Profile Columns to Understand Data in a Data Prep Recipe

In CRM Analytics, run column profiling on sample data to estimate key stats about columns. Column profiling is useful when combining data from different sources. It works on the latest available data, except for connected objects which may be based on outdated sample data.

To run a column profile, select the column and click . The Profile tab shows valid values, missing values, zero values, frequent values, and a histogram to understand the shape of the data.

The Attributes tab shows the label, API name, and data type of the selected column. It also indicates whether the column contains multiple values for dimension columns.

Column profiles are based on sample rows, not all rows in the recipe. They can help identify potential data quality issues and provide statistics such as counts, percentages, and averages.
title: Understanding Data Profiling in CRM Analytics
